{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Normal}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Bouffalant}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Normal|prevnum=625|prev=Bisharp|nextnum=627|next=Rufflet|roundleft=bl|roundright=br}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Bouffalant\n|jname=バッフロン\n|jtranslit=Baffuron\n|tmname=Buffron\n|category=Bash Buffalo\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Normal\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Reckless\n|ability2=Sap Sipper\n|abilityd=Soundproof\n|ndex=626\n|udex=132\n|u2dex=269\n|height-ftin=5\'03"\n|height-m=1.6\n|weight-lbs=208.3\n|weight-kg=94.5\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Field\n|eggcycles=20\n|expyield=172\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|gendercode=127\n|color=Brown\n|catchrate=45\n|evtotal=2\n|evat=2\n|body=08\n|pokefordex=bouffalant\n|generation=5\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Bouffalant\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'バッフロン\'\'\' \'\'Buffron\'\') is a {{type|Normal}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation V]].\n\nIt is not known to [[Evolution|evolve]] into or from any other Pokémon.\n\n==Biology==\nBouffalant is a bovine Pokémon with a large, dark {{wp|afro}} on its head. Two large, curving horns, each with two golden growths resembling rings, protrude from the afro. It has a shaggy brown hide that ends at its knees and does not cover its face. A large, gray nose sits at the end of its short, beige snout, and its yellow eyes are partly hidden by its hair. There are black tear markings directly below its eyes. Each of its beige legs has a single, gray hoof and its tail ends in a stubby tuft of fur. A territorial Pokémon, it will headbutt anyone that attempts to invade its territory. However, in the [[BW066|anime]], it has been known not to attack those with an afro hairstyle. Protected by its afro, which absorbs damage, its headbutts are strong enough to derail a train and send it flying. Bouffalant is the [[signature move|only known Pokémon]] to learn {{m|Head Charge}}.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Alder Bouffalant.png|thumb|250px|left|Bouffalant in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\n[[Alder]]\'s Bouffalant debuted in [[Trip]]\'s flashback \'\'[[BW031|Ash and Trip\'s Third Battle!]]\'\', where he remembered seeing it as a child, which inspired him to become a [[Pokémon Trainer]]. It physically debuted in \'\'[[BW052|Ash Versus the Champion!]]\'\', where it faced {{AP|Pikachu}} in a battle with {{Ash}}. Alder fell asleep during the battle, resulting in no one winning. Alder later used Bouffalant in a battle against Trip and his {{TP|Trip|Serperior}}, and he was able to win.\n\nA herd of Bouffalant appeared in \'\'[[BW066|Baffling the Bouffalant!]]\'\', where they attacked anyone in their territory who wasn\'t wearing an afro.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nA herd of Bouffalant was seen in the prologue of \'\'[[M14|White—Victini and Zekrom]]\'\'. They were startled by the arrival of a dust storm and began to stampede towards [[Luisa]]\'s village. However, the nearby [[Damon]] summoned [[Reshiram (M14)|Reshiram]] to easily destroy the dust storm, thus placating the Bouffalant in time.\n\nA Bouffalant appeared in \'\'[[BW053|A Maractus Musical!]]\'\', where it was taking part in the [[Pokémon Performance Competition]] alongside an {{p|Elgyem}}.\n\nMultiple Bouffalant appeared in \'\'[[M15|Kyurem VS. The Sword of Justice]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Bouffalant appeared in \'\'[[BW102|Team Eevee and the Pokémon Rescue Squad!]]\'\', where they were among the Pokémon living in a ranch at [[Virgil]]\'s house.\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Unova}}\n{{Animedexbody|BW052|Bouffalant|Ash\'s Pokédex|Bouffalant, the Bash Buffalo Pokémon. Bouffalant is powerful and destructive, wildly charging and {{m|Headbutt|headbutting}} everything in its path.}}\n{{Animedexbody|BW066|Bouffalant|Ash\'s Pokédex|Bouffalant, the Bash Buffalo Pokémon. While aggressively defending its territory, Bouffalant will charge anything and everything in its way.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Best Wishes\'\'|Unova}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Alder Bouffalant Adventures.png|thumb|200px|Bouffalant in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Be the Best! Pokémon B+W manga===\n{{tc|Rich Boy|Dol}} has a Bouffalant, which battled alongside his {{p|Swoobat}} in a Double Battle against [[Monta]].\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\n[[Alder]] has a Bouffalant, which was first seen carrying him over the water in order to take him to [[Nimbasa City]] in \'\'[[PS485|Gigi\'s Choice]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon RéBURST manga===\nA Bouffalant appears as the [[Burst]] form of Afron.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Bouffalant (TCG)}}\n\n==Other appearances==\n===\'\'{{mov|Detective Pikachu}}\'\'===\nA Bouffalant appeared in \'\'{{mov|Detective Pikachu}}\'\'.\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=normal}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=V}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=V|reg1=Unova|num1=132|label1={{gameabbrev5|BW}}:|reg2=Unova|num2=269|label2={{gameabbrev5|B2W2}}:}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Black|t=FFF|entry=Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=White|entry=They charge wildly and headbutt everything. Their headbutts have enough destructive force to derail a train.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Black 2|v2=White 2|t=FFF|entry=They are known to charge so wildly that if a train were to enter their territory, they would send it flying.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=Kalos|reg2=Hoenn}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=X|t=FFF|entry=They charge wildly and headbutt everything. Their headbutts have enough destructive force to derail a train.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Y|entry=Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Omega Ruby|t=fff|entry=They charge wildly and headbutt everything. Their headbutts have enough destructive force to derail a train.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Alpha Sapphire|t=fff|entry=Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VII|reg1=Alola|r